{"info": {"author": "Gerard Marull-Paretas", "author_email": "gerardmarull@gmail.com", "bugtrack_url": null, "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 3 - Alpha", "Intended Audience :: Developers", "License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python", "Topic :: Software Development :: User Interfaces"], "description": "========\nqtmodern\n========\n\n.. image:: https://travis-ci.org/gmarull/qtmodern.svg?branch=master\n    :target: https://travis-ci.org/gmarull/qtmodern\n    :alt: Travis build\n\n.. image:: https://img.shields.io/pypi/v/qtmodern.svg\n    :target: https://pypi.python.org/pypi/qtmodern\n    :alt: PyPI Version\n\n``qtmodern`` is a Python package aimed to make PyQt/PySide applications look\nbetter and consistent on multiple platforms. It provides a custom frameless\nwindow and a dark theme. In order to be compatible with multiple Python Qt\nwrappers `QtPy <https://github.com/spyder-ide/qtpy>`_ is used. The initial idea\ncomes from `this project <https://github.com/Jorgen-VikingGod/Qt-Frameless-Window-DarkStyle>`_.\n\n.. image:: examples/mainwindow.png\n    :width: 450px\n    :align: center\n    :alt: Example\n\nInstallation\n------------\n\nThe recommended way to install is by using ``pip``, i.e::\n\n    pip install qtmodern\n\nUsage\n-----\n\nIn order to use ``qtmodern``, simply apply the style you want to your\napplication and then, create a ``ModernWindow`` enclosing the window you want to\n*modernize*::\n\n    import qtmodern.styles\n    import qtmodern.windows\n\n    ...\n\n    app = QApplication()\n    win = YourWindow()\n\n    qtmodern.styles.dark(app)\n    mw = qtmodern.windows.ModernWindow(win)\n    mw.show()\n\n    ...", "description_content_type": "", "docs_url": null, "download_url": "", "downloads": {"last_day": -1, "last_month": -1, "last_week": -1}, "home_page": "https://www.github.com/gmarull/qtmodern", "keywords": "", "license": "MIT", "maintainer": "", "maintainer_email": "", "name": "qtmodern", "package_url": "https://pypi.org/project/qtmodern/", "platform": "", "project_url": "https://pypi.org/project/qtmodern/", "project_urls": {"Homepage": "https://www.github.com/gmarull/qtmodern"}, "release_url": "https://pypi.org/project/qtmodern/0.2.0/", "requires_dist": null, "requires_python": "", "summary": "Qt Widgets Modern User Interface", "version": "0.2.0", "yanked": false, "html_description": "<div class=\"project-description\">\n            <a href=\"https://travis-ci.org/gmarull/qtmodern\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img alt=\"Travis build\" src=\"https://warehouse-camo.ingress.cmh1.psfhosted.org/62092ee93748205ab01144a6b8196d5c05d12bb3/68747470733a2f2f7472617669732d63692e6f72672f676d6172756c6c2f71746d6f6465726e2e7376673f6272616e63683d6d6173746572\"></a>\n<a href=\"https://pypi.python.org/pypi/qtmodern\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img alt=\"PyPI Version\" src=\"https://warehouse-camo.ingress.cmh1.psfhosted.org/15c37c26523460e43dc0b1f6f3cfa8081172714c/68747470733a2f2f696d672e736869656c64732e696f2f707970692f762f71746d6f6465726e2e737667\"></a>\n<p><tt>qtmodern</tt> is a Python package aimed to make PyQt/PySide applications look\nbetter and consistent on multiple platforms. It provides a custom frameless\nwindow and a dark theme. In order to be compatible with multiple Python Qt\nwrappers <a href=\"https://github.com/spyder-ide/qtpy\" rel=\"nofollow\">QtPy</a> is used. The initial idea\ncomes from <a href=\"https://github.com/Jorgen-VikingGod/Qt-Frameless-Window-DarkStyle\" rel=\"nofollow\">this project</a>.</p>\n<img alt=\"Example\" class=\"align-center\" src=\"https://warehouse-camo.ingress.cmh1.psfhosted.org/bee1b37f0d74dccb0a4221394a64343ead9590af/6578616d706c65732f6d61696e77696e646f772e706e67\" width=\"450px\">\n<div id=\"installation\">\n<h2>Installation</h2>\n<p>The recommended way to install is by using <tt>pip</tt>, i.e:</p>\n<pre>pip install qtmodern\n</pre>\n</div>\n<div id=\"usage\">\n<h2>Usage</h2>\n<p>In order to use <tt>qtmodern</tt>, simply apply the style you want to your\napplication and then, create a <tt>ModernWindow</tt> enclosing the window you want to\n<em>modernize</em>:</p>\n<pre>import qtmodern.styles\nimport qtmodern.windows\n\n...\n\napp = QApplication()\nwin = YourWindow()\n\nqtmodern.styles.dark(app)\nmw = qtmodern.windows.ModernWindow(win)\nmw.show()\n\n...\n</pre>\n</div>\n\n          </div>"}, "last_serial": 6387612, "releases": {"0.1.0": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "75e86c5b46a3fe7f8a033f1f1a28d6a0", "sha256": "5f3239516d9fbba6992c713c0814e6c8778f640daf8ae8a22c76777d3d6cf6ef"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "qtmodern-0.1.0.tar.gz", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "75e86c5b46a3fe7f8a033f1f1a28d6a0", "packagetype": "sdist", "python_version": "source", "requires_python": null, "size": 4501, "upload_time": "2017-09-21T12:44:07", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2017-09-21T12:44:07.559334Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/18/8e/d504e2a06b47af4ea81c3f8908849a567eff48b75e9dda1a10106cea4c96/qtmodern-0.1.0.tar.gz", "yanked": false}], "0.1.1": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "cdab73469d4621bbbdd225b3dd5dbe11", "sha256": "bf9b2697990d43623308963a0ad9735e55979096223b3f265eedf97f72585216"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "qtmodern-0.1.1.tar.gz", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "cdab73469d4621bbbdd225b3dd5dbe11", "packagetype": "sdist", "python_version": "source", "requires_python": null, "size": 4504, "upload_time": "2017-09-24T09:30:33", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2017-09-24T09:30:33.240777Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/23/14/dde85848ff805288fc71fba94c35e748feebf6244a90e13bff3f67728329/qtmodern-0.1.1.tar.gz", "yanked": false}], "0.1.2": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "852a27ae9906f6c73b32772f83c489ad", "sha256": "91028d0f7e4f26e31deb1efe43398ce99e884d158aebc5f76abac3c2c7d0a3e3"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "qtmodern-0.1.2.tar.gz", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "852a27ae9906f6c73b32772f83c489ad", "packagetype": "sdist", "python_version": "sour